title: House of Cards
plot: Majority House Whip Francis Underwood takes you on a long journey as he exacts his vengeance on those he feels wronged him - that is, his own cabinet members including the President of the United States himself. Dashing, cunning, methodical and vicious, Frank Underwood along with his equally manipulative yet ambiguous wife, Claire, take Washington by storm through climbing the hierarchical ladder to power in this Americanized recreation of the BBC series of the same name.
awards: Top Rated TV #95 | Won 2 Golden Globes. Another 32 wins & 215 nominations.
stars: Kevin Spacey, Michel Gill, Robin Wright, Kate Mara

similars.title: Narcos
similars.plot: A chronicled look at the criminal exploits of Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar, as well as the many other drug kingpins who plagued the country through the years.
similars.stars: Pedro Pascal, Wagner Moura, Boyd Holbrook

similars.title: True Detective
similars.plot: Seasonal anthology series in which police investigations unearth the personal and professional secrets of those involved, both within and outside the law.
similars.stars: Vince Vaughn, Colin Farrell, Rachel McAdams

similars.title: Dexter
similars.plot: By day, mild-mannered Dexter is a blood-spatter analyst for the Miami police. But at night, he is a serial killer who only targets other murderers.
similars.stars: Michael C. Hall, Jennifer Carpenter, David Zayas

similars.title: Mindhunter
similars.plot: Set in the late 1970s, two FBI agents are tasked with interviewing serial killers to solve open cases.
similars.stars: Jonathan Groff, Holt McCallany, Anna Torv

similars.title: Sherlock
similars.plot: A modern update finds the famous sleuth and his doctor partner solving crime in 21st century London.
similars.stars: Benedict Cumberbatch, Martin Freeman, Una Stubbs

similars.title: Westworld
similars.plot: Set at the intersection of the near future and the reimagined past, explore a world in which every human appetite can be indulged without consequence.
similars.stars: Evan Rachel Wood, Jeffrey Wright, Ed Harris

similars.title: Fargo
similars.plot: Various chronicles of deception, intrigue and murder in and around frozen Minnesota. Yet all of these tales mysteriously lead back one way or another to Fargo, North Dakota.
similars.stars: Billy Bob Thornton, Martin Freeman, Allison Tolman

similars.title: Black Mirror
similars.plot: An anthology series exploring a twisted, high-tech multiverse where humanity's greatest innovations and darkest instincts collide.
similars.stars: Daniel Lapaine, Hannah John-Kamen, Michaela Coel

similars.title: House of Cards
similars.plot: The schemes of a ruthlessly ambitious British politician who will stop at nothing to get to the top.
similars.stars: Ian Richardson, Susannah Harker, Miles Anderson

similars.title: Chernobyl
similars.plot: In April 1986, an explosion at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant in the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics becomes one of the world's worst man-made catastrophes.
similars.stars: Jessie Buckley, Jared Harris, Stellan Skarsgård

similars.title: Breaking Bad
similars.plot: A high school chemistry teacher diagnosed with inoperable lung cancer turns to manufacturing and selling methamphetamine in order to secure his family's future.
similars.stars: Bryan Cranston, Aaron Paul, Anna Gunn

similars.title: Game of Thrones
similars.plot: Nine noble families fight for control over the lands of Westeros, while an ancient enemy returns after being dormant for millennia.
similars.stars: Emilia Clarke, Peter Dinklage, Kit Harington
